OL,3,CBritish prisons crisis sees Guernsey
OL,4,Cforced to deal with more inmates
OL,6,FThroughout last year, it held a daily
OL,7,Faverage of 90 prisoners, rising from
OL,8,Fan average of 79 in 2023.
OL,10,FJohn de Carteret, Guernsey's Prison
OL,11,FGovernor, has partly blamed
OL,12,F"significant accommodation issues" in
OL,13,FEnglish and Welsh prisons, as inmates
OL,14,Facross the Channel Islands wait to be
OL,15,Ftransferred to the UK to serve their
OL,16,Fsentences.
OL,18,FIn the report, he states: "The prison
OL,19,Fcertainly held more individuals who,
OL,20,Fin the absence of transfer issues,
OL,21,Fwould have been moved off-island.
